**Fix 1 (Line 46)**: `variant={ButtonVariant.plain}` — The `plain` variant exists in both the old and new type unions. No code change needed.

**Fix 2 (Line 42)**: The `<Button>` on lines 42-57 contains both an icon (`<KialiIcon.Warning />`) AND text (the `<span>` with open issue count). Per the fix instructions for icon + text: move just the icon to the `icon` prop, keep the text as children.

Current code:
```tsx
<Button
  id={'icon_warning'}
  aria-label={t('System Error')}
  onClick={props.toggleSystemErrorsCenter}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
>
  <KialiIcon.Warning />

  <span className={systemErrorCountStyle}>
    {t('{{count}} Open Issue', {
      count: props.systemErrorsCount,
      defaultValue_one: '{{count}} Open Issue',
      defaultValue_other: '{{count}} Open Issues'
    })}
  </span>
</Button>
```

Should become:
```tsx
<Button
  id={'icon_warning'}
  aria-label={t('System Error')}
  onClick={props.toggleSystemErrorsCenter}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  icon={<KialiIcon.Warning />}
>
  <span className={systemErrorCountStyle}>
    {t('{{count}} Open Issue', {
      count: props.systemErrorsCount,
      defaultValue_one: '{{count}} Open Issue',
      defaultValue_other: '{{count}} Open Issues'
    })}
  </span>
</Button>
```

